<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" type="nesting">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Nesting.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Unknown but most likely nesting in the sandy hummocks. At localities along the coast, sampled by F. W. and S. K. Gess, the species was found principally 
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="58" start="start">associated</pageBreakToken>
with the sandy hummocks formed around 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Brownanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Brownanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Psilocaulon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Psilocaulon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schlechter &amp; Diels" authorityYear="1907" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Zygophyllaceae" genus="Zygophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="clavatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Zygophyllum clavatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and visiting the flowers of these plants.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="prey">
